<TITLE> DSE crosses new benchmark </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, September 2 (bdnews24.com) The main DGEN or general index on the Dhaka Stock Exchange crossed the 2500-point mark in midday trade Sunday, triggered by a rally in the shares of banks. An amendment in the Banking Companies Act 1991approved by the government last weekallowing banks to raise capital requirements up to Tk 2.0 billion from Tk 1.0 billion continues to buoy bank stocks. Banks with capital less than Tk 1.0 billion moved up the most with prices of some banks touching a new level. Power shares fell on profit taking. The DGEN added 54.68 points or 2.22 percent to reach 2510.53 at 12.18 pm. The DSI or all-share price index rose 49.89 points or 2.42 percent to 2109.61. A total of 3,857,600 shares worth Tk 1.11 billion were traded while 69 issues gained, 78 fell and 17 remained unchanged. BRAC Bank, AB Bank and City Bank led the market at 12.10 pm. BRAC Bank surged to a record high of Tk 1120 from Wednesday's close of Tk 1050.75. AB Bank also touched a high point at Tk 2387.25 from Wednesday's Tk 2170.25. City Bank rallied to Tk 780.5 from Tk 678.75. Power Grid fell to Tk 609.25 from Tk 615.75. DESCO declined to Tk 1128 from Tk 1142.5. Prime Bank fell on reports of a share scam. One Bank, National Bank, Pubali Bank and Mutual Trust Bank rallied. bdn
